Interface CommandLineToolProvider


  • public interface CommandLineToolProvider
    A command line tool provider if available.
    Since:
    0.5

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Static Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      static CommandLineToolProvider from(Supplier<CommandLineTool> toolSupplier)
      Creates a provider from the specified command line tool supplier.

    • Method Detail

      • get

        CommandLineTool get()
        Returns the command line tool provided by this provider.
        Returns:
        a CommandLineTool instance or throws IllegalArgumentException if no command line tool can be provided.

      • isAvailable

        boolean isAvailable()
        Returns the availability of the command line tool providered.
        Returns:
        true if the command line tool is available or false otherwise.

      • of

        static CommandLineToolProvider of(CommandLineTool tool)
        Creates a fixed provider of the specified command line tool. Calling get() will return the specified command line tool.
        Parameters:
        tool - a command line tool to provide.
        Returns:
        a CommandLineToolProvider instance for the specified tool

      • unavailable

        static CommandLineToolProvider unavailable()
        Creates an unavailable provider. Calling get() will throw an exception.
        Returns:
        a CommandLineToolProvider instance that is unavailable.

      • from

        static CommandLineToolProvider from(Supplier<CommandLineTool> toolSupplier)
        Creates a provider from the specified command line tool supplier. Calling get() will throw an exception only if the supplier returns null.
        Parameters:
        toolSupplier - a supplier for the tool provided.
        Returns:
        a CommandLineToolProvider instance for the specified tool supplier.
